-- A2A's Adviser Intesa Sanpaolo Gives Options for Edison Stake, Il Sole Says
-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 2010-09-25T09:45:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-25/a2a-s-adviser-intesa-sanpaolo-gives-options-for-edison-stake-il-sole-says.html
A2A SpA ’s sale of its stake in
 Edison SpA , Italy’s second-largest utility, is one of six
options suggested by its financial adviser, daily Il Sole 24 Ore
reported, citing a report prepared by  Intesa Sanpaolo SpA.   Intesa said A2A would have difficultly securing funds to
buy the shares it doesn’t already own in Edison, Il Sole
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
